## Part 4: Coverage and Quality (1 hour)

### 4.1 Code Coverage

```bash
# Generate coverage
go test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./module/user

# View coverage by function
go tool cover -func=coverage.out

# Open in browser
go tool cover -html=coverage.out

# Check threshold
go test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./module/user
COVERAGE=$(go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep total | awk '{print int($3)}')
if [ $COVERAGE -lt 80 ]; then
    echo "Coverage below 80%: $COVERAGE%"
    exit 1
fi
```

### 4.2 Healthy Coverage

**Targets:**
- Overall: 70-80% (more than enough)
- Business logic: 90%+
- Handlers: 70%
- Data layers: 80%+

**Don't aim for 100%** - some code doesn't need testing:
- Simple getters
- Error cases from external libraries
- Platform-specific code

### 4.3 Linting and Quality

```bash
# Format code
go fmt ./...

# Lint for common issues
go vet ./...

# More thorough linting
go install github.com/golangci/golangci-lint/cmd/golangci-lint@latest
golangci-lint run ./...

# Run before committing
go fmt ./...
go vet ./...
go test ./...
```

